      "summary": "Causes shigellosis, an acute, self-limited febrile diarrhea that typically lasts 7 days if untreated. It is an important cause of morbidity and mortality in young children in low- and middle-income countries. Outbreaks, often with resistant strains, are linked to international travel and occur in specific populations like MSM.",
